\t\tManchester United transfer news: Red Devils OUT of the race to sign Ajax captain Matthijs de Ligt – reports  

\t\t
\t\tThe Netherlands international was reportedly close to moving to Old Trafford in a £70million deal 
\t 
\t 



\t
\t
\t\t\t\t\t
\t\t\t\t
\t\t\t\t\tBy Joe Coleman\t\t\t\t 
\t\t\t 
\t\t
\t\t
\t\t\t
\t\t\t\t26th May 2019, 
\t\t\t\t10:41 am 
\t\t\t 

\t\t\t\t\t
\t\t\t\tUpdated: 26th May 2019, 
\t\t\t\t11:36 am 
\t\t\t 
\t\t\t\t 

\t 
 
\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t
\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tMatthijs De Ligt will NOT be moving to Manchester United this summer, according to reports. 
Rumours about the Ajax captain moving to Old Trafford in a £70million deal began to gather momentum over the weekend.  

\t

\t\t Matthijs De Ligt now seems set for a move to Barcelona   

\t\t\t\t
\t\t\tgetty\t\t 
\t\t
\t\t\t\t
\t\t\t1  
\t\t 
\t\t\t 

\t\t
\t\tMatthijs De Ligt now seems set for a move to Barcelona\t 
\t 

However, Sky Sports are now claiming the United hierarchy fear the 19-year-old is set to sign for Barcelona instead. 
De Ligt was a regular for Ajax over the past three seasons and captained the club to a Eredivisie and cup double this campaign. 
Make sure you stay up to date with all the latest transfer news and gossip by following talkSPORT’s live blog.  
He was also instrumental in the Dutch side’s run to the Champions League semi-finals – suffering defeat to Tottenham in the last four of the competition. 
After Barca’s defeat to Valencia in the Copa del Rey and collapse at the same stage in Europe, Barcelona president Josep Bartomeu confirmed the Spanish club were working on departures from the Nou Camp as well as incoming transfers. 
